BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 2151.032 of the Revised Code be 5
enacted to read as follows: 6
Sec. 2151.032. (A) No child whose parent, guardian, or 7
custodian allows the child to engage in independent activities 8
without adult supervision shall, solely for that reason, be 9
considered to be an abused or neglected child, provided that 10
both of the following apply: 11
(1) The independent activities are appropriate based on 12
the child's age, maturity, and physical and mental abilities. 13
(2) The lack of supervision does not constitute conduct 14
that is so grossly negligent as to endanger the health or safety 15
of the child. 16
(B) As used in this section, "independent activities" 17
include any of the following: 18
(1) Traveling to and from school or nearby commercial or 19

